Install dependencies:
Copysudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install libx11-dev libxext-dev libbsd-dev

Download MinilibX:
You can either clone the repository or download it from the official website.
Using git:
Copygit clone https://github.com/42Paris/minilibx-linux.git

Navigate to the downloaded directory:
Copycd minilibx-linux

Compile the library:
Copymake

Install the library:
Copysudo cp mlx.h /usr/include
sudo cp libmlx.a /usr/lib
